title: N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 9 §§ 1642-1.4 - Numbering of checks
content:
N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 9 §§ 1642-1.4 - Numbering of checks

State Regulations

Checks shall be prenumbered, consecutively, in a
separate series for each fund and bank account. Checks voided should be stamped
cancelled and stapled to the stub of the check book so that all checks can be
accounted for. Notes
N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 9

1642-1.4
